---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base
  title="Data sources — Ringdocket"
  description="The public sources Ringdocket ingests. FTC complaints today; FCC enforcement and ITG tracebacks where accessible."
>
  <main class="prose-page">
    <p class="kicker mono">Record</p>
    <h1>What we ingest, and where it comes from.</h1>
    <p class="lead">
      Most spam-blocker apps run a closed list. You install, you trust, you
      hope. We don't ask for that. Every number on the public block list
      either came from corroborated user reports or from a public
      government source we can cite by URL. This page lists every source.
    </p>

    <h2>Live in V1</h2>

    <section class="source">
      <header class="source-head">
        <p class="source-name">FTC National Do Not Call Registry &mdash; consumer complaints</p>
        <p class="source-meta mono">86,519 complaints ingested as of 2026-04-29</p>
      </header>
      <p>
        The Federal Trade Commission publishes consumer complaints filed
        against numbers that violate Do Not Call rules. The dataset is in the
        public domain under 17 U.S.C. &sect;105. Our cron pulls the feed daily,
        normalizes the phone numbers to E.164, and writes them to our
        corroboration store. A single FTC complaint counts as a corroborated
        signal &mdash; the FTC does the verification work for us.
      </p>
      <p class="source-cite mono">
        Attribution required where the data is displayed:
        "Includes data from the FTC National Do Not Call Registry."
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="source">
      <header class="source-head">
        <p class="source-name">User reports through the iOS app</p>
        <p class="source-meta mono">Three accounts, fourteen days, distinct devices and /24 subnets</p>
      </header>
      <p>
        A report from one user is a flag. Three reports about the same
        number from three distinct accounts within a rolling 14-day window,
        with no two sharing a device fingerprint or an IP /24 &mdash; that
        promotes to the public block list. Notes attached to a report stay
        private; only the number, category, and timestamp ever leave the
        moderation layer.
      </p>
    </section>

    <h2>Planned, not yet shipped</h2>

    <section class="source pending">
      <header class="source-head">
        <p class="source-name">FCC enforcement actions</p>
        <p class="source-meta mono">attribution badges on takedowns</p>
      </header>
      <p>
        When the FCC publicly cites or fines a campaign, we want that fact
        attached to every number associated with it &mdash; an "attributed
        takedown" badge that says, in plain language, who took it down and
        when. Today we draft that copy by hand from press releases. Phase 4
        plans an automated ingest of the FCC enforcement index.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="source pending">
      <header class="source-head">
        <p class="source-name">Industry Traceback Group (ITG) tracebacks</p>
        <p class="source-meta mono">if the public listing remains accessible</p>
      </header>
      <p>
        ITG publishes traceback summaries identifying which carriers
        originated specific spam campaigns. If the public listing stays
        accessible, we will attribute originating-carrier data on campaign
        pages. If access closes, we say so &mdash; we don't fake the
        attribution.
      </p>
    </section>

    <h2>The block list is public</h2>
    <p>
      The current public block list is served as JSON at
      <a href="https://blocklist.ringdocket.com/current.json" class="mono">
        blocklist.ringdocket.com/current.json
      </a>.
      Anyone can fetch it, audit it, or build something else on top of it
      under the terms in our
      <a href="/terms">Terms of Service</a>. The corroboration record behind
      every number is visible from
      <a href="/methodology">our methodology page</a>.
    </p>

    <p class="bottom-note">
      If you find a public dataset we should be ingesting, email
      <a href="mailto:hello@ringdocket.com">hello@ringdocket.com</a>. The
      strongest pitches link to a stable URL and a non-restrictive license.
    </p>
  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  .prose-page {
    max-width: 720px;
    margin: 0 auto;
    padding: clamp(2rem, 5vw, 4rem) clamp(1rem, 3vw, 2rem) 5rem;
  }
  .kicker {
    font-size: 0.75rem;
    color: var(--accent-signal);
    text-transform: uppercase;
    letter-spacing: 0.1em;
    margin: 0 0 0.875rem;
  }
  h1 {
    font-family: 'Bricolage Grotesque';
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: clamp(2rem, 4.5vw, 2.875rem);
    line-height: 1.05;
    letter-spacing: -0.02em;
    color: var(--ink-primary);
    margin: 0 0 1.25rem;
  }
  h2 {
    font-family: 'Bricolage Grotesque';
    font-weight: 700;
    font-size: 1.375rem;
    margin: 2.75rem 0 1rem;
    color: var(--ink-primary);
  }
  .lead {
    font-family: 'Newsreader';
    font-size: 1.125rem;
    line-height: 1.6;
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
    max-width: 60ch;
    margin: 0 0 1.5rem;
  }
  p {
    font-family: 'Newsreader';
    font-size: 1rem;
    line-height: 1.65;
    color: var(--ink-secondary);
    max-width: 64ch;
  }
  .source {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding: 1.25rem 0 0.5rem;
    margin-top: 1.25rem;
  }
  .source.pending {
    opacity: 0.85;
  }
  .source-head {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
  }
  .source-name {
    font-family: 'Inter Tight';
    font-weight: 500;
    font-size: 1rem;
    color: var(--ink-primary);
    margin: 0;
  }
  .source-meta {
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    color: var(--ink-byline);
    margin: 0.25rem 0 0;
  }
  .source-cite {
    font-size: 0.6875rem;
    color: var(--ink-byline);
    background: var(--surface-inset);
    padding: 0.5rem 0.75rem;
    border-radius: 4px;
    margin-top: 0.75rem;
  }
  a {
    color: var(--ink-primary);
    border-bottom: 1px solid var(--rule);
    text-decoration: none;
  }
  a:hover {
    border-bottom-color: var(--ink-primary);
  }
  .mono {
    font-family: 'JetBrains Mono';
    font-size: 0.8125rem;
  }
  .bottom-note {
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: 0.9375rem;
    color: var(--ink-byline);
    margin-top: 2rem;
  }
</style>
